Program: Outlook
Title: 12/04/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00qbnm5
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 13 Apr 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, Jo Fidgen meets Cedella Marley, the eldest child of Jamaican musician Bob Marley. She talks about why he was the ultimate competitive dad, how he wrote a song for her and about her own recent achievements designing the kit for the Jamaican Olympic team. Also today, Rusiko and Georgi, two Georgian refugees who were forced to flee from Abkhazia 20 years ago describe how they managed to survive in a time of war. (Image: Bob Marley. Credit: AP) Show less